clinical_study.brief_title: A Research Study for Patients With Overactive Bladder

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to investigate whether injections of botulinum toxin Type A into the bladder are safe and effective in treating overactive bladder.

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.measure: Change in Number of Urinary Urge Incontinence Episodes
primary_outcome.description: Mean number of urinary urge incontinence episodes measured over a 7-day diary prior to week 12. Urinary urge incontinence is defined as urinary leakage associated with a strong desire to urinate.

secondary_outcome.description: Mean number of micturitions measured over a 7 day diary prior to each visit. Micturation is defined as urinating into the toilet.

secondary_outcome.measure: Change in Number of Nocturia Episodes
secondary_outcome.description: Mean number of nocturia episodes measured over a 7 day diary prior to each visit. A nocturia episode is a void (urinating into the toilet) that interrupts one's sleep.

secondary_outcome.measure: Maximum Cystometric Capacity (MCC) by Urodynamic Measurements
secondary_outcome.description: Maximum Cystometric Capacity (maximum volume that the bladder can hold) measured in mean milliliters

Measured on 3 domains; a 5-point scale (1-5) for each domain. Sum of the domain scores is normalized to a scale of 0-100 (100 = no impact of incontinence on daily activities, 0 = maximum impact of incontinence on daily activities). Mean scores presented.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Must be between 18-85 years old
- Must have been diagnosed by his/her doctor with overactive bladder at least 6 months ago
- Must weigh at least 50 kg (110 lbs)
- Must be willing and able to record information regarding bladder function into a diary (provided)
- Must be willing and able to complete the entire course of the study
Exclusion Criteria:
- Cannot currently be catheterizing as a way to control incontinence
- Must not have used botulinum toxin type A or any other botulinum toxin previously for any condition
